In the mixins.database, the get_options method does not check the upper+lower combinations: we do an «upper» in the key checking and not during the split so a «database_options» would not match the split.

This should be easy to fix but I set the issue to do it later.

```python
# django-kaio/kaio/mixins/database.py
    def get_options(self):
        options = {}
        for key in opts.keys():
            if 'DATABASE_OPTIONS_' in key.upper():
                options[str(key.split('DATABASE_OPTIONS_')[1].lower())] = get(key)
        return options
