In [section 4.e](http://www.adobe.com/devnet/opentype/afdko/topic_feature_file_syntax.html#4.e), the OpenType Feature File specification writes: “You may not use the script or language keywords within a named lookup block.” However, makeotf v2.0.90 accepts the following input:
```
languagesystem DFLT dflt;
feature test {
    lookup L {
        script grek;
        pos T 100;
    } L;
} test;
```

Should makeotf reject the above file, because it is in violation of the current spec? Or should the spec be changed, and say that script/language _are_ permitted inside named lookup blocks in case they happen to be placed inside a feature block?

Since the construct it getting used in existing feature files (we’ve seen such feature files getting emitted by the Glyphs.app font editor), it might be safer to change the spec. On the other hand, there might be an advantage to keeping the spec clean — it’s already a pretty complex language, and allowing exceptions to general rules won’t make it any easier.

